    "This paper presents an audit of medical treatment approaches for Cushing's disease across nine international Pituitary Tumors Centers of Excellence (PTCOEs) between 2018-2020.",
    "The study focuses on real-world clinical practice data for medical management of Cushing's disease, which complements clinical trial data.",
    "Ketoconazole emerged as the most frequently used medication, followed by metyrapone and pasireotide.",
    "Overall biochemical control rates were 75% across all medical treatments, with some variation by specific drug."
